---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "FireCMS Terms of Service";
const description = "Terms and conditions for using FireCMS services.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

  <main>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="relative isolate overflow-hidden bg-linear-to-br from-black to-gray-900 pt-24 pb-16 sm:pt-32 sm:pb-24 lg:pt-40 lg:pb-16 border-b border-gray-800">
      <div class="absolute inset-x-0 -top-40 -z-10 transform-gpu overflow-hidden blur-3xl sm:-top-80" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="blob-shape relative left-[calc(50%-11rem)] aspect-1155/678 w-144.5 -translate-x-2/3 rotate-30 bg-linear-to-tr from-primary to-blue-900 opacity-15 sm:left-[calc(50%-30rem)] sm:w-288.75"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="px-4 mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center lg:px-12">
        <h1 class="mb-8 text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight leading-none md:text-6xl text-white font-sans">
          Terms of Service
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-400">Last updated: October 12, 2025</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Content Section -->
    <section class="bg-black py-16 sm:py-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="prose prose-lg prose-invert max-w-none">
          <div class="space-y-8 text-gray-300">
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
              <p class="mb-4">
                By accessing or using FireCMS ("Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree to these Terms, do not use the Service.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4">2. Description of Service</h2>
              <p class="mb-4">
                FireCMS provides a headless CMS framework and cloud service for managing Firebase and MongoDB databases. The Service includes both:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
                <li><strong>FireCMS Cloud:</strong> A hosted service for accessing your Firebase/MongoDB databases</li>
                <li><strong>FireCMS Open Source:</strong> A self-hosted framework licensed under MIT License</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4">3. User Accounts</h2>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 mt-6">3.1 Account Creation</h3>
              <p class="mb-4">
                You must provide accurate and complete information when creating an account. You are responsible for maintaining the security of your account credentials.
              </p>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 mt-6">3.2 Account Responsibilities</h3>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
                <li>You are responsible for all activities under your account</li>
                <li>You must notify us immediately of any unauthorized access</li>
                <li>You must not share your account credentials</li>
                <li>You must comply with all applicable laws and regulations</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4">4. Data Ownership and Responsibility</h2>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 mt-6">4.1 Your Data</h3>
              <p class="mb-4">
                You retain all ownership rights to your content data. FireCMS does not claim ownership of any data you store in your Firebase or MongoDB databases.
              </p>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 mt-6">4.2 Your Responsibilities</h3>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
                <li>You are responsible for backing up your data</li>
                <li>You are responsible for compliance with data protection laws (GDPR, CCPA, etc.)</li>
                <li>You are responsible for the content you store and manage</li>
                <li>You must not use the Service for illegal purposes</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4">5. Acceptable Use</h2>
              <p class="mb-4">You agree not to:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
                <li>Violate any laws or regulations</li>
                <li>Infringe on intellectual property rights</li>
                <li>Transmit malicious code or malware</li>
                <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to the Service</li>
                <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Service</li>
                <li>Use the Service to harm minors</li>
                <li>Engage in any fraudulent activity</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4">6. Pricing and Payment</h2>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 mt-6">6.1 Fees</h3>
              <p class="mb-4">
                Certain features of the Service require payment. Pricing is available at <a href="/pricing" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-light">firecms.co/pricing</a>.
              </p>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 mt-6">6.2 Billing</h3>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
                <li>Fees are billed in advance on a monthly or annual basis</li>
                <li>All fees are non-refundable except as required by law</li>
                <li>You authorize us to charge your payment method</li>
                <li>We may change pricing with 30 days notice</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4">7. Intellectual Property</h2>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 mt-6">7.1 Open Source Components</h3>
              <p class="mb-4">
                The FireCMS open-source framework is licensed under the MIT License. The hosted Service and certain premium features are proprietary.
              </p>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 mt-6">7.2 Service Content</h3>
              <p class="mb-4">
                All Service-related content, trademarks, and intellectual property are owned by FireCMS or our licensors.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4">8. Termination</h2>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 mt-6">8.1 By You</h3>
              <p class="mb-4">
                You may terminate your account at any time through your account settings.
              </p>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 mt-6">8.2 By Us</h3>
              <p class="mb-4">
                We may suspend or terminate your account if you violate these Terms or for any other reason at our discretion, with or without notice.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4">9. Disclaimers</h2>
              <p class="mb-4">
                THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4">10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
              <p class="mb-4">
                TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, FIRECMS SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS OF PROFITS OR REVENUES, WHETHER INCURRED DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY, OR ANY LOSS OF DATA, USE, GOODWILL, OR OTHER INTANGIBLE LOSSES.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4">11. Indemnification</h2>
              <p class="mb-4">
                You agree to indemnify and hold harmless FireCMS from any claims, damages, losses, liabilities, and expenses arising from your use of the Service or violation of these Terms.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4">12. Governing Law</h2>
              <p class="mb-4">
                These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the jurisdiction where FireCMS is registered, without regard to its conflict of law provisions.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4">13. Changes to Terms</h2>
              <p class="mb-4">
                We reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. We will notify users of material changes via email or through the Service. Continued use of the Service after changes constitutes acceptance of the new Terms.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4">14. Contact Information</h2>
              <p class="mb-4">
                For questions about these Terms, please contact us at:
              </p>
              <p class="mb-2">Email: <a href="mailto:legal@firecms.co" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-light">legal@firecms.co</a></p>
              <p class="mb-2">Contact page: <a href="/contact" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-light">firecms.co/contact</a></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

</Layout>
